<div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">
  <h4>How do I configure my application to use Binnacle?</h4>
  <p>Below is a summary of what we've done for this sample application in order to use Binnacle.</p>
</div>

<div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">
  <h4>Gemfile</h4>
  <p>
    In the Gemfile you'll need the <strong><a href="https://github.com/binnacle-io/binnacle-ruby" target="blank">binnacle</a></strong> Gem
    (available on <a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/binnacle" target="blank">Rubygems</a>) along with
    the gems for the <strong><a href="https://github.com/binnacle-io/binnacle_chat" target="blank">binnacle_chat</a></strong> and
    <strong><a href="https://github.com/binnacle-io/binnacle_ar" target="blank">binnacle_ar</a></strong> widgets.
  </p>
  

  <figure class="highlight">
    <pre>
      <code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby">
gem 'binnacle', '~> 0.4.7'
gem 'binnacle_chat', '~> 0.0.8'
gem 'binnacle_ar', '~> 0.0.2'

source 'https://rails-assets.org' do
  gem 'rails-assets-jquery-ui', '~> 1.11.3'
  gem 'rails-assets-jspanel', '~> 2.6.1'
  gem 'rails-assets-gravatarjs', '~> 1.0.0'
  gem 'rails-assets-remarkable-bootstrap-notify', '~> 3.1.3'
  gem 'rails-assets-highcharts', '~> 4.2.3'
end
      </code>
    </pre>
  </figure>

  <p>
    The binnacle_chat widget requires the <strong><a href="https://github.com/components/jqueryui" target="blank">JQuery UI</a></strong>,
    <strong><a href="http://jspanel.de/" target="blank">JSPanel</a></strong> and
    <strong><a href="https://github.com/mazondo/gravatarjs" target="blank">Gravatar</a></strong> JS libraries which we also pull from Rails Assets.
  </p>
  <p>
    For the Web Push and Realtime Demos we pull in <strong><a href="http://bootstrap-notify.remabledesigns.com" target="blank">Bootstrap Notify</a></strong> and
    <strong><a href="http://www.highcharts.com" target="blank">Highcharts</a></strong>.
  </p>

    <figure class="highlight">
    <pre>
      <code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby">
source 'https://rails-assets.org' do
  gem 'rails-assets-jquery-ui', '~> 1.11.3'
  gem 'rails-assets-jspanel', '~> 2.6.1'
  gem 'rails-assets-gravatarjs', '~> 1.0.0'
  gem 'rails-assets-remarkable-bootstrap-notify', '~> 3.1.3'
  gem 'rails-assets-highcharts', '~> 4.2.3'
end
      </code>
    </pre>
  </figure>
</div>

<div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">
  <h4>Binnacle Environment Variables</h4>
  <p>
    If you deployed the application using the <img src="https://www.herokucdn.com/deploy/button.svg"/> button.
    The required environment variables are already configured on your behalf.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you want to run the application locally you would need to configure the values below.
    We recommend using a .env file via <strong><a href="https://github.com/bkeepers/dotenv" target="blank">dotenv-rails</a></strong> (already in the Gemfile).
  </p>
  <p>
    The values for <code>BINNACLE_CHAT_CHANNEL</code> and <code>BINNACLE_AR_CHANNEL</code> can be set to the same
    channel id or you can create extra channels for each of the widgets.
  </p>
  <p>
    The values for <code>BINNACLE_ACCT_ID</code>, <code>BINNACLE_APP_ID</code>, <code>BINNACLE_APP_LOG_CHANNEL_ID</code> and <code>BINNACLE_APP_ERR_CHANNEL_ID</code>
    are used for convenience to generate links to navigate back to <a href="https://binnacle.io" target="blank">binnacle.io</a>. Their values are the integer numbers you'll see
    at the end URLs in binnacle.io such as <code>/accounts/8/apps/16</code> (where <code>8</code> is <code>BINNACLE_ACCT_ID</code> and 16 is <code>BINNACLE_APP_ID</code>).
    <strong>They are not critical for the functioning of the Showcase app.</strong>
  </p>
  <figure class="highlight">
    <pre>
      <code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby">
BINNACLE_ENDPOINT=api1.binnacle-api.io # pick from api1..api6
BINNACLE_APP=...
BINNACLE_API_KEY=...
BINNACLE_API_SECRET=...
BINNACLE_APP_LOG_CHANNEL=...
BINNACLE_APP_ERR_CHANNEL=...
BINNACLE_CHAT_CHANNEL=...
BINNACLE_AR_CHANNEL=...
BINNACLE_ACCT_ID=...
BINNACLE_APP_ID=...
BINNACLE_APP_LOG_CHANNEL_ID=...
BINNACLE_APP_ERR_CHANNEL_ID=...
      </code>
    </pre>
  </figure>
</div>

<div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">
  <h4>Binnacle Initializer</h4>
  <p>
    The Binnacle Initializer can be created using the Rails Generator (<code>rails generate binnacle</code>). The generator creates a
    file under config/initializers/binnacle.rb. Although you can configure all aspects of the binnacle client via this initializer we
    recommend that you configure any credentials and account/app/channel ids via Environment variables
  </p>
  <figure class="highlight">
    <pre>
      <code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby">
Binnacle.configure do |config|
  config.intercept_rails_logging = true
  config.report_exceptions = true
end
      </code>
    </pre>
  </figure>
  <p>
    At a minimum the binnacle initializer needs to call the configure method with no parameters in order for Binnacle to bootstrap itself in your app:
  </p>
  <figure class="highlight">
    <pre>
      <code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby">
Binnacle.configure
      </code>
    </pre>
  </figure>
</div>
